Package: pactR
Type: Package
Title: Posterior Analysis of Coalescent Trees
Version: 0.9.4
Date: 2026-05-26
Authors@R: c(
    person("Trevor", "Bedford", email = "t.bedford@ed.ac.uk",
           role = c("aut"), comment = "Original C++ author"),
    person("PACT R Package Maintainer", role = c("cre"),
           email = "lambodhar1@gmail.com"))
Description: An R interface to PACT (Posterior Analysis of Coalescent Trees),
    a tool for interpreting and manipulating labeled evolutionary trees from
    coalescent inference programs such as BEAST, Migrate, IM, and LAMARC.
    PACT reads posterior samples of genealogical trees in NEWICK format and
    computes structured coalescent statistics including TMRCA, coalescent rates,
    migration rates, nucleotide diversity, FST, Tajima's D, and spatial
    diffusion coefficients. Time-windowed (skyline) versions of all statistics
    and per-tip analyses are also supported. The package wraps the original C++
    implementation via Rcpp and provides helper functions to read analysis
    outputs into R data frames.
